Here is an example of how to use JavaScript and a backend language like Node.js to collect user input and store it in a database:
```
// Get the user input from the form
const userInput = document.getElementById("user-input").value;

// Send the user input to the backend server
fetch("/backend-api", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
  },
  body: JSON.stringify(userInput)
})
.then(response => response.json())
.then(data => {
  // Store the user input in the database
  const database = require("./database");
  database.storeUserInput(data);
})
.catch(error => console.error(error));
```

